    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Place settings or other combinations of cups, saucers, and plates that were given as a traditional gift on the occasion of a person's first solemn communion, which was a rite of passage among young adults in some Christian denominations. The items are typically made of porcelain or silver. The dishes are distinguished by decoration or text commemorating the event.</Note_Text>
